      "replayEndSec": 25.705613,
      "narrationText": "Healthy infrastructure starts with a healthy workstation. We scan the local environment for configuration issues -- Node.js version, SSH key presence, and KVM virtualization readiness.",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/monitoring-tutorial/monitoring-tutorial-01.12e24277.mp3",
      "audioDurationSec": 13.165714,
      "stepLabel": "Step 1: Run diagnostics"
    },
    {
      "id": "monitoring-tutorial-02",
      "markerIndex": 1,
      "replayStartSec": 25.705613,
      "replayEndSec": 37.199979,
      "narrationText": "Local environment clear. Now we check the remote machine over SSH. You'll see uptime, disk and memory usage, SMART disk health, container counts, and service status.",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/monitoring-tutorial/monitoring-tutorial-02.56778847.mp3",
      "audioDurationSec": 10.919184,
      "stepLabel": "Step 2: System overview"
    },
    {
      "id": "monitoring-tutorial-03",
      "markerIndex": 2,
      "replayStartSec": 37.199979,
      "replayEndSec": 47.874153,
      "narrationText": "To see every running container across all isolated Docker daemons on the machine, we pull a unified view -- with state, health checks, CPU, and memory per container.",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/monitoring-tutorial/monitoring-tutorial-03.0ae8f87f.mp3",
      "audioDurationSec": 10.997551,
      "stepLabel": "Step 3: View running containers"
